<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q36_v12_item" title="Q36_v12" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceA</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float">
    <qti-default-value>
      <qti-value>0</qti-value>
    </qti-default-value>
  </qti-outcome-declaration>
  <qti-item-body>
    <p>Considera el siguiente sistema de ecuaciones:</p>
    <div>
      <m:math>
        <m:mrow>
          <m:mo>{</m:mo>
          <m:mtable>
            <m:mtr>
              <m:mtd>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mtd>
            </m:mtr>
            <m:mtr>
              <m:mtd>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>11</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mtd>
            </m:mtr>
          </m:mtable>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math>
    </div>
    <p>En la siguiente lista se muestran cuatro pares ordenados candidatos a solución:</p>
    <p>
      A:
      <m:math>
        <m:mrow>
          <m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math><br />
      B:
      <m:math>
        <m:mrow>
          <m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math><br />
      C:
      <m:math>
        <m:mrow>
          <m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math><br />
      D:
      <m:math>
        <m:mrow>
          <m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math>
    </p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="false" max-choices="1">
      <qti-prompt>Observa los cuatro pares ordenados A, B, C y D. ¿Cuál de ellos es solución del sistema anterior?</qti-prompt>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">A<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! Al reemplazar x = 2 e y = 1 en el sistema, se obtiene 2·2 + 1 = 4 + 1 = 5 y también 4·2 + 3·1 = 8 + 3 = 11. Como satisface las dos ecuaciones, el par (2, 1) sí es solución.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">B<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Al reemplazar x = 1 e y = 3, la primera ecuación sí se cumple porque 2·1 + 3 = 2 + 3 = 5, pero la segunda no se cumple porque 4·1 + 3·3 = 4 + 9 = 13, y 13 ≠ 11. Por eso, (1, 3) no es solución del sistema.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">C<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Al reemplazar x = 5 e y = −3, la primera ecuación da 2·5 + (−3) = 10 − 3 = 7, y 7 ≠ 5. Además, la segunda da 4·5 + 3·(−3) = 20 − 9 = 11. Como no satisface ambas ecuaciones al mismo tiempo, (5, −3) no es solución del sistema.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">D<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Al reemplazar x = 3 e y = −1, la primera ecuación da 2·3 + (−1) = 6 − 1 = 5, pero la segunda da 4·3 + 3·(−1) = 12 − 3 = 9, y 9 ≠ 11. Por eso, (3, −1) no es solución del sistema.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso por verificación de pares ordenados</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Recordar la condición para ser solución</strong></p>
            <p>Un par ordenado es solución del sistema solo si cumple simultáneamente las dos ecuaciones.</p>
            <p>El sistema es:</p>
            <m:math>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mo>{</m:mo>
                <m:mtable>
                  <m:mtr>
                    <m:mtd>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mtd>
                  </m:mtr>
                  <m:mtr>
                    <m:mtd>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>11</m:mn>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mtd>
                  </m:mtr>
                </m:mtable>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Probar la opción A</strong></p>
            <p>Si <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> e <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>, entonces:</p>
            <p>Primera ecuación:</p>
            <m:math>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
            <p>Segunda ecuación:</p>
            <m:math>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>8</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>11</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
            <p>La opción A cumple ambas ecuaciones.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Verificar que las otras opciones no sirven</strong></p>
            <p><em>Opción B:</em> <m:math><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></p>
            <p>Primera ecuación:</p>
            <m:math>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
            <p>Segunda ecuación:</p>
            <m:math>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>9</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>13</m:mn><m:mo>≠</m:mo><m:mn>11</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
            <p>No cumple el sistema.</p>
            <p><em>Opción C:</em> <m:math><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></p>
            <p>Primera ecuación:</p>
            <m:math>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>10</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>7</m:mn><m:mo>≠</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
            <p>No cumple el sistema.</p>
            <p><em>Opción D:</em> <m:math><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></p>
            <p>Primera ecuación:</p>
            <m:math>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>6</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
            <p>Segunda ecuación:</p>
            <m:math>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>12</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>9</m:mn><m:mo>≠</m:mo><m:mn>11</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
            <p>Tampoco cumple el sistema.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>El único par ordenado que satisface las dos ecuaciones es <m:math><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math>. Por lo tanto, la respuesta correcta es la alternativa A.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>